It depends on who is saying things, who is being referred to, and if the person saying it is a third party.
Vorist (as in eating) covers any situation where the two have different eating needs. There would be grades and using the full range of prefixes & suffixes should define things nicely.
Different genus or order? I'd make up a word using the Latin. So a wolf that is prejudiced against humans and all other primates might be an ordoist.

This is basic worldbuilding through language. You have a decent technical term (such as the previous) and then corrupt it into something like ordie (or-dee)
We do it all the time with slang to shorthand or reference a person/event, which I'm really guilty of.
